[2
Date: 22, Sept, 1999
From: "Claude Lavigne" <clavigne@EM.AGR.CA>
Subject: Bluetongue in Canada

Thanks for your diligence in obtaining accurate information of this very
important topic. Matt's comments are accurate but I would add two areas of
clarifications.
1) We have had 4 incursions in the Okanagan Valley since 1975.
2) What he refers to as "imported instances" were not clinical cases but
only serological cases and in none of these cases to my knowledge is there
evidence that seroconversion occurred in Canada.
---
Claude Lavigne
<clavigne@EM.AGR.CA>
